 :tx/provenance :observed
 :tx/rationale "Create task: CCE-5: Concept-aware steering responses — observe and status as latent space navigation. CONTEXT: The deepest architectural insight: every braid CLI response is a STEERING VECTOR injected into the LLM's context window, shaping attention and exploration direction. The CLI is a Markov blanket between the store (persistent model) and the LLM (transient model). braid status is not a dashboard — it is a prompt. braid observe response is not an acknowledgment — it is a navigation aid. The quality of these responses determines the agent's entire trajectory. RATIONALE: DOGFOOD responsiveness scored 2.7/10 because responses were receipts ('recorded +9 datoms') or templates ('Does X interact with Y?'). The fix: responses are FUNCTIONS OF THE CONCEPT GRAPH — conditioned on concept membership, structural gaps, and exploration trajectory. APPROACH: TWO SURFACES. (A) braid observe response (observe.rs ~150 LOC change). After observation is stored and concept assignment runs: Line 1: concept membership — 'joined concept:event-processing (3 members)' or 'new concept forming: error-handling (2 members, needs 1 more to crystallize)'. Line 2: structural gap — computed from entity auto-links: 'this concept spans events/, materialize/ — but not cascade/ (adjacent, unexplored)'. Uses import graph from bootstrap packages or simple adjacency from shared entity references. Line 3: steering question — computed from concept topology: take current concept, find nearest concept that shares no entities (via embedding distance), ask about the boundary. Template: 'what connects {current_concept.name} to {nearest_concept.name}?' or if no other concepts exist: 'what other aspects of {mentioned_entities} are worth investigating?'. The question is specific (uses concept names and package names), falsifiable (the agent can go look), and structurally derived (not a template). (B) braid status response (status.rs ~100 LOC change). When concepts exist: show concept inventory — 'concepts: event-processing (5 obs), error-handling (3 obs, cross-cutting), bilateral-cycle (2 obs)'. Show coverage — 'coverage: 12/38 packages explored (concepts span 8 subsystems)'. Show frontier — 'frontier: cascade, projector, causal (imported by explored packages)'. When fresh store with innate schemas: show innate schema progress — 'schemas: components (38 detected, 0 explored), dependencies (0 mapped), invariants (0 verified), patterns (0 identified), anomalies (0 found)'. Fade innate schemas after 10+ observations (replaced by emergent concepts). (C) Coverage computation: query :exploration/mentions-entity to find which packages have observations. Subtract from total packages (from bootstrap). Frontier = packages that are adjacent-to (imported-by or import) observed packages but not yet observed. If no import graph, frontier = packages in same directory as observed ones. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After observe on fresh store, response includes innate schema assignment. (B) After 3+ observations in same concept, response names the concept and shows member count. (C) Structural gap identifies at least one unexplored adjacent entity. (D) Steering question uses concept names and entity names (not session IDs). (E) Status shows concept inventory when concepts exist. (F) Status shows coverage ratio and frontier on external projects. (G) Innate schemas fade from status after 10+ domain-specific observations. (H) All existing observe and status tests pass. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs, crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs. DEPENDS-ON: CCE-4 (entity auto-linking), CCE-2 (concept entities). TRACES-TO: ADR-FOUNDATION-019 (Universal Action Queue — the steering question IS the acquisition function rendered as natural language), INV-CONVERGENCE-008 (responsive observation)."
